    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026-02",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The 13-factor credibility assessment demonstrates that 7 factors were formally assessed and all met their required levels under MRL 2 for the adult normothermic CPB operating envelope validated in 2022–2023. Six factors were not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping per ASME V&V 40 Table 1. The credibility package is accepted for the original intended use. The team notes that the operating envelope was expanded in Q4 2025 to include pediatric patients and low-flow assist conditions not covered by the existing validation evidence. Re-validation studies addressing the expanded envelope are planned for H1 2026. The current acceptance is conditioned on the understanding that the expanded envelope use cases remain provisional until re-validation evidence is available and linked.",
